<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/1195</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_WF1">White</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-15">October 15,
                                        1931</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Minister of Guatemala, Dr. <persName corresp="#p_RA1">Recinos</persName>, and the Minister of Honduras, Dr. <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName>, called to exchange
                                ratifications of the treaty and additional convention regarding the
                                arbitration of their boundary dispute. They exchanged the
                                ratifications and signed a protocol to this effect, copies of which
                                they also exchanged.</p>
                            <p>They left with me a note to the Secretary of State enclosing copies
                                of the Treaty and Additional Act and asking that they be transmitted
                                to the Chief Justice, advising him of the exchange of ratifications
                                and of his designation as Presiding officer of the arbitral
                                tribunal.</p>
                            <p>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_RLS1">Rowe</persName> was also present, as
                                was Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SSY1">Sidney Smith</persName>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WF1">F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>]
                                            W[<hi rend="smallcaps">hite</hi>]</persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>